What is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the muscle fiber. What is the basic structural unit of skeletal muscle tissue? The basic structural unit of skeletal muscle tissue is the sarcomere. What is the basic functional unit of smooth muscle tissue? The basic functional unit of smooth muscle tissue is the myocyte. What is the basic structural unit of smooth muscle tissue? The basic structural unit of smooth muscle tissue is the cell.
